‚≠ê Launching a Website on AWS (2 Methods)

1Ô∏è‚É£ Static Website ‚Üí AWS S3 (Best for HTML/CSS/JS)
2Ô∏è‚É£ Dynamic Website ‚Üí EC2 (Node.js, PHP, Django, etc.)

Dono explain kar raha hoon.

üü¢ METHOD 1: Launch STATIC Website using S3 (HTML/CSS/JavaScript)
‚úî Step 1: Create S3 Bucket

Login AWS

Open S3

Click Create Bucket

Bucket Name:
my-website-shyam

Region: Choose nearest

Uncheck "Block all public access"

Create bucket

‚úî Step 2: Upload Your Website Files

Click on bucket ‚Üí Upload

Upload:

index.html

style.css

images/

‚úî Step 3: Enable Static Website Hosting

S3 Bucket ‚Üí Properties

Scroll ‚Üí Static Website Hosting

Enable

Enter:

Index document: index.html

Save

‚úî Step 4: Make Files Public

Select all files

Actions ‚Üí Make public

Or attach this bucket policy:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::my-website-shyam/*"
    }
  ]
}

‚úî Step 5: Get Website Link

Properties ‚Üí Static Hosting URL

Example:

http://my-website-shyam.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com


üéâ Your website is LIVE!

üü† METHOD 2: Launch DYNAMIC Website using EC2 (Node.js, React, PHP, Django, etc.)
‚≠ê Step 1: Launch EC2 Instance

EC2 Dashboard ‚Üí Launch Instance

Name: my-web-server

OS:
‚úî Ubuntu 22.04

Instance Type:
‚úî t2.micro (Free tier)

Create Key Pair

Configure Security Group:

Type	Port	Purpose
SSH	22	Server Login
HTTP	80	Website Access
HTTPS	443	SSL

Launch

‚≠ê Step 2: Connect to EC2 (SSH)
Windows PowerShell:
ssh -i "mykey.pem" ubuntu@<Public-IP>

‚≠ê Step 3: Install Required Software
For static hosting (Apache):
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt install apache2 -y

For Node.js App:
sudo apt install nodejs npm -y

For Python App:
sudo apt install python3-pip -y

For PHP:
sudo apt install apache2 php libapache2-mod-php -y

‚≠ê Step 4: Upload Your Website Files
Option 1: SCP (simple)
scp -i "mykey.pem" index.html ubuntu@<Public-IP>:/var/www/html/

Option 2: Directly edit inside EC2:
sudo nano /var/www/html/index.html

‚≠ê Step 5: Start & Enable Web Server
Apache:
sudo systemctl start apache2
sudo systemctl enable apache2

Node.js:
node app.js

‚≠ê Step 6: Open Website in Browser
http://<EC2-Public-IP>


üéâ Your Dynamic Website is LIVE on AWS!

üí° BONUS: Make Website Public with Domain Name (Optional)
1. Buy domain from:

AWS Route53

GoDaddy

Namecheap

2. Add DNS record:

Type: A record
Value: EC2 Public IP

Example:

www.mywebsite.com  ‚Üí  54.201.123.45

üéØ Final Summary (Exam Ready Notes)
Method	Best For	Service Used
AWS S3	Static Websites (HTML/CSS/JS)	S3 Bucket + Static Hosting
AWS EC2	Dynamic Websites (Node/PHP/Python)	EC2 + Web Server

Steps:

Launch instance/bucket

Upload website files

Configure security/permissions

Test with browser URL